Agriculture Principal Secretary Hamadi Boda has asked Kwale residents to adopt fruit farming to fight poverty. The PS said many farmers prefer planting maize, which does not have good yields resulting in food insecurity. He spoke on Sunday at Kilole Primary School during an education forum of 400 students who joined Form One through scholarship for Base Titanium mining company. Bright students from poor homes will benefit from the Sh17 million programme. sponsors bright students who scored 300 and above marks and comes from poor families. “Crops do well in specific types of soil. In Kwale, the soil is suitable for fruit farming, especially citrus fruits,” Boga said.  